article.description: — Trevon Reddish scored 23 points as Presbyterian defeated South Carolina Upstate 75-65 on Monday night.
article.headline: Presbyterian beats South Carolina Upstate 75-65
article.story: CLINTON, S.C. -- — Trevon Reddish scored 23 points as Presbyterian defeated South Carolina Upstate 75-65 on Monday night. Rayshon Harrison added 22 points for the Blue Hose (7-12, 5-10 Big South Conference). Reddish hit 8 of 10 shots. Harrison also had eight rebounds. Kobe Stewart had six steals for Presbyterian Everette Hammond had 19 points for the Spartans (4-16, 4-10). Nevin Zink added 15 points. Khydarius Smith had 10 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
